# Ansible Roles

This directory will contain reusable Ansible roles for common tasks.

## Planned roles:

### Network Device Roles
- `netbox-device` - Configure devices based on NetBox data
- `network-backup` - Backup network device configurations
- `vlan-management` - Manage VLANs across infrastructure

### Infrastructure Roles
- `proxmox-vm` - Provision and manage Proxmox VMs
- `container-deploy` - Deploy and configure containers
- `monitoring-agent` - Deploy monitoring agents

### NetBox Integration Roles
- `netbox-sync` - Synchronize data with NetBox
- `netbox-inventory` - Generate inventory from NetBox
- `netbox-compliance` - Check compliance against NetBox data

### Security Roles
- `hardening` - Apply security hardening
- `certificate-management` - Manage TLS certificates
- `firewall-config` - Configure firewall rules

## Creating New Roles

Use `ansible-galaxy role init <role_name>` to create the standard structure:
```
roles/
└── role_name/
    ├── defaults/
    │   └── main.yml
    ├── handlers/
    │   └── main.yml
    ├── meta/
    │   └── main.yml
    ├── tasks/
    │   └── main.yml
    ├── templates/
    ├── tests/
    │   ├── inventory
    │   └── test.yml
    └── vars/
        └── main.yml
```